wdi-FM.LBL.BMNY.IR.ZS.def: Broad money (IFS line 35L..ZK) is the sum of currency outside banks; demand deposits other than those of the central government; the time, savings, and foreign currency deposits of resident sectors other than the central government; bank and traveler’s checks; and other securities such as certificates of deposit and commercial paper.
wdi-FM.LBL.BMNY.IR.ZS.name: Broad money to total reserves ratio
wdi-FM.LBL.BMNY.IR.ZS.source: International Monetary Fund, International Financial Statistics and data files.
